  "_about": "Math operation → EXECUTABLE form across sympy / MATLAB / Wolfram — the 'man file' that connects the canonical equations' symbols to programming. Two jobs: (1) document how each math symbol maps to code so a flattened PDF symbol (∫, Σ, √, ∂) is unambiguous; (2) let the compute arm turn a canonical equation into executable sympy directly (the bridge canon → verified-compute), instead of the LLM cold-translating. sympy is our executor; MATLAB/Wolfram columns are the cross-reference the canonical references (Wolfram MathWorld / MATLAB Symbolic Math Toolbox) document.",
